## §1 Terminal goal — real-semantics formal closure of 4 F-CL-FORMAL axes

The lean4 mechanical layer at `~/core/hexa-meta/formal/lean4/`
proves 4 closure-machinery theorems over hexa-bio's WEAVE composition.

| Axis | Theorem name | Statement | Status (2026-05-12 cycle-30) |
|------|--------------|-----------|---------------|
| F-CL-FORMAL-1 | `sigma_lattice_card` | `sigma 6 = 12` | **REAL-SEMANTICS PROVEN** (`sigma` is a computable Nat divisor-sum; `rfl`) |
| F-CL-FORMAL-2 | `landauer_monotonic` | `heatConsumed (compose floor s₁ s₂) ≥ max …` | ✅ **PROVEN against WEAVE-semantics v4** (2026-05-12 cycle-30++++++, hexa-meta `7c0ec92`; v3 baseline `9e44e75`) — substrate-polymorphic over `[AddCommGroup E] [LinearOrder E] [IsOrderedAddMonoid E]` (modern unbundled spelling of linearly-ordered abelian group). `heat : E` (was `ℝ`); opaque positive `floor : E` via section variable + `[Fact (0 < floor)]` (was `kT · Real.log 2`); `LandauerPass floor s := s.heat ≥ s.bits_erased • floor` (Nat-smul). All 3 bonus theorems re-proved with direct lemma calls (`le_trans`/`add_le_add`/`sub_le_sub_right`/`nsmul_nonneg`/`add_nsmul`/`abel`; linarith too weak for abstract ordered group). `landauer_monotonic` uses `le_add_of_nonneg_right/_left`. Imports: dropped `Real.Basic`/`Log.Basic`/`NormNum`; added `Algebra.Order.Group.Defs`/`Monoid.Defs`/`Monoid.Unbundled.Pow`/`Tactic.Abel`. Consumers recover v3 by `E := ℝ`, `floor := kT * Real.log 2`. v5 stretch: parametrise ring/module structure on E. |
| F-CL-FORMAL-3 | `pi_p2_verifier_terminates` | `∃ n, verifierSteps q ≤ n` | ✅ **PROVEN against WEAVE-semantics v4** (2026-05-12 cycle-30++++++, hexa-meta `7c0ec92`; v3 baseline `2680f88`) — `verifierStepsLex` recurses on `Prod.lex` tuple `(depth, sz)` over `Nat × Nat` (was single-Nat structural recursion in v3). Three branches: base `(0, 0) → payload`; scan `(0, sz'+1) → 1 + verifierStepsLex sz' 0 p` (lex right decreases); branch `(d'+1, sz) → 2 * verifierStepsLex sz d' p` (lex left decreases). Termination via Mathlib's `WellFoundedRelation` instance for `Prod.lex`, invoked through `termination_by (depth, sz)` + `decreasing_by` with `Prod.Lex.left` / `Prod.Lex.right` constructors (simp_wf normalises). v3 fallback `verifierStepsRec` retained; `verifierStepsLex_eq_v3` proves numerical equivalence. Equation lemmas (`verifierStepsLex_scan`/`_branch`) added because WF-recursion doesn't unfold by rfl. Closed-form `verifierStepsLex sz d p = 2^d * (sz + p)` re-proved via depth-outer induction + `verifierStepsLex_depth_zero` (size-inner induction). Same witness as v3. Mathlib imports added: `Order.WellFounded`/`Order.Lex`/`Data.Prod.Lex`. v5 stretch: verifier-strategy typeclass (recursion shape + measure as data; consumer contract quantifies over ANY strategy). |
| F-CL-FORMAL-4 | `closure_cert_idempotent` | `∀ c : ClosureCert α β [DecidableEq α] [DecidableEq β] [CommMonoid β], discloseTwice c = discloseOnce c` | ✅ **PROVEN against WEAVE-semantics v4** (2026-05-12 cycle-30++++++, hexa-meta `7c0ec92`; v3 baseline `9e44e75`) — `structure ClosureCert (α : Type) [DecidableEq α] (β : Type) [DecidableEq β] [CommMonoid β]`: first-class caveat payloads. `caveat_bag : Finset (α × β)` (was `Finset α` in v3); `signer_set` unchanged (signers carry no payload). `addCaveat` takes `(k : α) → (v : β)` — non-idempotent monoid means different payloads for same key COEXIST as separate entries (raw_91 honest C3: Finset-pair tradeoff vs Finsupp-based v5 that would collapse keys). NEW `totalCaveatPayload : ClosureCert α β → β` aggregates via `Finset.prod` (CommMonoid `·*·` / `1`). 5 v3 theorems re-proved + NEW `addCaveat_commutative` bonus (`Finset.insert_comm`). Imports added: `Algebra.BigOperators.Group.Finset.Basic`. v5 stretch: Finsupp payload that collapses entries with the same key via the monoid `*` structure. |

**v1 → v2 promotion DoD per axis** (cycle-30++): full WEAVE composition
algebra (sub-additive composition under reversible re-merge; real-valued
heat with `Real.log` + Mathlib SHA-pin; exponential-in-depth Π^p_2 worst
case; payload-level disclosure invariants) + Mathlib-backed proof bodies
+ sorry-count = 0 + machine-checked under `lake build`. The v1 → v2 work
is **NOT a v1.x closure blocker** — by design, the v1.x cert surrogate
is the `raw_91_c3_disclose:MVP_caveat` disclosure (per `.roadmap.weave`
